## Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/xray-agent.git
cd xray-agent
```

### 2. Create and activate a virtual environment

```bash
python -m venv venv

# Mac/Linux
source venv/bin/activate

# Windows
venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 3. Install Python dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Install Poppler (required for PDF support)

**Windows:**
Download from [poppler-windows releases](https://github.com/oschwartz10612/poppler-windows/releases), extract to `C:\poppler`, and add `C:\poppler\Library\bin` to your system PATH.

**Mac:**
```bash
brew install poppler
```

**Linux:**
```bash
sudo apt install poppler-utils
```

### 5. Set up your API key

Create a `.env` file in the root folder:

```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
```

Get your free API key at [aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com).

### 6. Run the app

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

## Deploying to Streamlit Cloud

1. Push your code to GitHub (`.env` is gitignored — never pushed)
2. Go to [streamlit.io/cloud](https://streamlit.io/cloud) and connect your repo
3. In **Settings → Secrets**, add:
   ```
   GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
   ```
4. Streamlit Cloud will automatically install Poppler from `packages.txt`

